    "Top: synthetic datasets used for pre-training; bottom: human datasets used in our experiments.",
    "The two metrics FDA (Fixation Duration Accuracy) and FLA (Fixation Location Accuracy) are computed as follows:",
    "where T pred is the predicted fixation duration, and T ground denotes the ground-truth fixation duration;",
    "where X pred and Y pred respectively indicate the predicted fixation of x and the predicted fixation of y, and X ground and Y ground indicate the ground-truth fixation of x and the ground-truth fixation of y.",
    "Whenever the model perfectly predicts a scanpath, both FDA and FLA are set to 1, hence avoiding dividing by zero."
